    {
      "text": "A 34-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with right-upper-quadrant pain that started 2 hours after dinner, has increased in intensity during the past hour, and is now persistent. She also reports nausea and diaphoresis but no heartburn, diarrhea, constipation, melena, or rectal bleeding. She has never had this pain before. She denies eating late, trying new medications, or using any nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drugs.\nShe has a normal body temperature, a heart rate of 121 beats per minute, a blood pressure of 146/98 mm Hg, and an oxygen saturation of 98% while breathing ambient air. Other than tachycardia, her cardiac and pulmonary examinations are normal. She has pain in the right upper quadrant with palpation but no Murphy sign (halted inspiration due to pain during palpation of the right upper quadrant).\nHer complete blood count, lipase level, and liver enzyme levels are normal. An ultrasound of the right upper quadrant is normal, including a normal gallbladder without stones or sludge.\nThe pain resolves within 3 hours, and the patient is able to eat a small meal without pain. She is discharged home.\nDuring the next 2 months, she has intermittent episodes of the same pain, typically in the evening, although it is not as intense as the first episode. Her laboratory results remain normal, and a stool antigen test for Helicobacter pylori is negative. A proton pump inhibitor is initiated and maintained for 6 weeks but does not improve her symptoms.\nUpper endoscopy and endoscopic ultrasound (which included the gallbladder) are normal. Cholecystokinin-stimulated cholescintigraphy reveals a gallbladder ejection fraction of 25% (normal, ≥40%).\nWhich one of the following next steps is most appropriate for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Start a tricyclic antidepressant"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Refer for endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography with placement of a biliary stent"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Refer for cholecystectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Order gastric scintigraphy"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Start erythromycin"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>A <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_N05dg&anker=Z1ac38cdc312662760e7dcb2548983f5b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_N05dg\" data-anker=\"Z1ac38cdc312662760e7dcb2548983f5b\" data-section-id=\"IncYu10\" data-sememe-id=\"8QaOB4\">tricyclic antidepressant</a> would be recommended if this patient had epigastric <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uq0pZh&anker=Z457e399b2dac47d79ac6962ff0546be5\" data-learningcard-id=\"uq0pZh\" data-anker=\"Z457e399b2dac47d79ac6962ff0546be5\" data-sememe-id=\"HzbK8w\">dyspepsia</a>) after negative testing (or treatment) for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=K80Un3&anker=Z17d93c9e0f6fa05e4fd06024276842d8\" data-learningcard-id=\"K80Un3\" data-anker=\"Z17d93c9e0f6fa05e4fd06024276842d8\">Helicobacter pylori infection</a>, an unsuccessful trial of a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rm0fSg&anker=Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-learningcard-id=\"rm0fSg\" data-anker=\"Z2753e50142e2f5b7089b165accdcc900\" data-sememe-id=\"ML0Myg\">proton pump inhibitor</a>, and an unremarkable <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=f80kN3&anker=Z1a617ceb3d8b9832108168a091314359\" data-learningcard-id=\"f80kN3\" data-anker=\"Z1a617ceb3d8b9832108168a091314359\" data-sememe-id=\"kj0m0T\">upper endoscopy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5I0iWh&anker=Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-learningcard-id=\"5I0iWh\" data-anker=\"Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-section-id=\"PL1WBh0\" data-sememe-id=\"ty0XSi\">Endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5I0iWh&anker=Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-learningcard-id=\"5I0iWh\" data-anker=\"Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-section-id=\"PL1WBh0\" data-sememe-id=\"ty0XSi\">ERCP</a>) can be considered in patients who have evidence of <span data-sememe-id=\"quWCHM0\">biliary obstruction</span> or a history of possible <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EI08eh&anker=Zadbad41cbbc269305367530ca790aac8\" data-learningcard-id=\"EI08eh\" data-anker=\"Zadbad41cbbc269305367530ca790aac8\" data-sememe-id=\"nRb7nt\">sphincter of Oddi dysfunction</a>. It does not have a role in the evaluation or treatment of functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>This patient, who has biliary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> without <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Z24c1b4e4cd23b046bd3ef10a99007d74\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Z24c1b4e4cd23b046bd3ef10a99007d74\" data-section-id=\"2FcThV0\" data-sememe-id=\"RV1l8f0\">gallstones</a> or other structural pathology, meets the Rome IV diagnostic criteria for functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder.<br><br>Biliary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> is usually described as severe, lasting between 30 minutes and several hours, and is not usually relieved by bowel movements or acid suppression. It often occurs intermittently over several months, and although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">nausea</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">vomiting</a>, and <span data-sememe-id=\"AQXRAB\">bloating</span> support the diagnosis, the presence of these secondary symptoms alone does not suggest biliary origin. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">Pain</a> that is not relieved by position change and that awakens the patient is also suggestive. The diagnosis of functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder in patients with biliary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> is supported by normal imaging, normal levels of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=260T4S&anker=Zb4592cc9a760c08db00e5b2e0bcb8d80\" data-learningcard-id=\"260T4S\" data-anker=\"Zb4592cc9a760c08db00e5b2e0bcb8d80\" data-section-id=\"fFckhV0\" data-sememe-id=\"tCXXFZ0\">pancreatic enzymes</a>, and a low <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xyb9dw\">ejection fraction</a> (&lt;40%) on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SJ0ytS&anker=Zf9ef5a19f529fed9aaf6130feb567007\" data-learningcard-id=\"SJ0ytS\" data-anker=\"Zf9ef5a19f529fed9aaf6130feb567007\" data-section-id=\"AL1RZ30\" data-sememe-id=\"5fbi5G\">cholescintigraphy</a>.<br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Z24c1b4e4cd23b046bd3ef10a99007d74\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Z24c1b4e4cd23b046bd3ef10a99007d74\" data-section-id=\"2FcThV0\" data-sememe-id=\"RV1l8f0\">Gallstones</a>, gravel, and sludge should be excluded with abdominal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a>, which is often repeated to ensure that small stones or sludge are not missed; in this case, an <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z72e0e4ca671451e34b6fb1ca2f6bbd84\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z72e0e4ca671451e34b6fb1ca2f6bbd84\" data-section-id=\"DPX1Sy\" data-sememe-id=\"NMa-KO\">endoscopic ultrasound</a> was performed, serving the same function. If the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Za228f7063cc6978b8577156d4f796a28\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Za228f7063cc6978b8577156d4f796a28\" data-section-id=\"UFcbhV0\" data-sememe-id=\"9QcNyX0\">common bile duct</a> is not visible on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a>, other imaging modalities such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5I0iWh&anker=Z614861aae12a058744d8cce73468b6db\" data-learningcard-id=\"5I0iWh\" data-anker=\"Z614861aae12a058744d8cce73468b6db\" data-section-id=\"PL1WBh0\" data-sememe-id=\"gR0Fmf\">magnetic resonance cholangiopancreatography</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5I0iWh&anker=Z614861aae12a058744d8cce73468b6db\" data-learningcard-id=\"5I0iWh\" data-anker=\"Z614861aae12a058744d8cce73468b6db\" data-section-id=\"PL1WBh0\" data-sememe-id=\"gR0Fmf\">MRCP</a>) should be considered to ensure there is no dilation of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-section-id=\"2FcThV0\" data-sememe-id=\"lpXvp_\">bile</a> ducts, which would suggest either an anatomical or functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-section-id=\"2FcThV0\" data-sememe-id=\"lpXvp_\">bile</a> duct problem. Other disorders should also be excluded, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uq0pZh&anker=Z457e399b2dac47d79ac6962ff0546be5\" data-learningcard-id=\"uq0pZh\" data-anker=\"Z457e399b2dac47d79ac6962ff0546be5\" data-sememe-id=\"HzbK8w\">dyspepsia</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SS0y_2&anker=Z6dc222965ad0be9a5f2c005b35e25334\" data-learningcard-id=\"SS0y_2\" data-anker=\"Z6dc222965ad0be9a5f2c005b35e25334\" data-section-id=\"2C0TrR\" data-sememe-id=\"1302hf\">pancreatitis</a>, and <span data-sememe-id=\"Z7VZ4D0\">ischemic heart disease</span> (especially if the patient has relevant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> and epigastric <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>).<br><br><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EI08eh&anker=Zadbad41cbbc269305367530ca790aac8\" data-learningcard-id=\"EI08eh\" data-anker=\"Zadbad41cbbc269305367530ca790aac8\" data-sememe-id=\"nRb7nt\">Sphincter of Oddi dysfunction</a> should be considered when patients have biliary-type <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> but is less likely in this case, given the patient’s normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> enzyme levels, lack of a dilated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Z4d90dfc94eec0585c748e9b6c6899d95\" data-section-id=\"2FcThV0\" data-sememe-id=\"lpXvp_\">bile</a> duct, and low <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xyb9dw\">ejection fraction</a>.<br><br>The recommended treatment for patients with functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder and a low <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xyb9dw\">ejection fraction</a> (&lt;40%) is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kG0mzh&anker=Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-learningcard-id=\"kG0mzh\" data-anker=\"Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-sememe-id=\"4eb3_s\">cholecystectomy</a>. Studies suggest that such patients are more likely to benefit from <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kG0mzh&anker=Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-learningcard-id=\"kG0mzh\" data-anker=\"Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-sememe-id=\"4eb3_s\">cholecystectomy</a> than patients with a normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xyb9dw\">ejection fraction</a> or atypical symptoms.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The recommended treatment for a patient with confirmed functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder and a low <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zo0reS&anker=Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"zo0reS\" data-anker=\"Zaf47fa64ad72a116818056dda3938b7b\" data-section-id=\"tpcXrW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Xyb9dw\">ejection fraction</a> (&lt;40%) is <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kG0mzh&anker=Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-learningcard-id=\"kG0mzh\" data-anker=\"Z3486fd991ff5fe473eaf21f11207abc3\" data-sememe-id=\"4eb3_s\">cholecystectomy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Gastric <span data-sememe-id=\"Q1bugs\">scintigraphy</span> can be used to evaluate for <span data-sememe-id=\"Nib-7t\">gastroparesis</span>, but this is typically characterized by a history of persistent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">nausea</a> that occurs with eating.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zb6aa0417ebf4b5441cad8f5d05d884bd\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zb6aa0417ebf4b5441cad8f5d05d884bd\" data-section-id=\"Sjcy-X0\" data-sememe-id=\"MOaMGk\">Erythromycin</a> can be used to increase gastric and intestinal motility, but it does not have a clear role in treating functional <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> disorder.</div>",
