      "text": "A 32-year-old man presents with 6 weeks of watery diarrhea, reporting 5–7 bowel movements daily without blood or mucus. He denies significant abdominal pain and has been maintaining a stable weight. He has a 10-year history of Crohn’s disease and underwent a limited ileal resection 6 months ago. He is taking mesalamine regularly and denies missed doses. Stool culture and Clostridioides difficile toxin assay are negative. Serum thyroid function tests and fecal fat measurement are normal. Colonoscopy shows no active inflammation of the remaining intestine.\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
